{"type":"message","id":"be784147","parentId":"c10b1313","timestamp":"2026-03-07T00:38:45.174Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1772843876510\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"+19194133445\",\n  \"sender\": \"Danny\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-06 19:37 EST\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Danny (+19194133445)\",\n  \"id\": \"+19194133445\",\n  \"name\": \"Danny\"\n}\n```\n\nTolui must use the local ollama abliterated model. And kublai must not have visibility into messages going to or from tolui. I want to be able to tag tolui with @ and then open a direct line of communication with him in signal, so that the message gets to him directly without routing via kublai. I want his response to go back to signal without being routed via kublai either. Use horde-brainstorming to design a way to do this, and let me know if it’s not possible under those constraints. Do not implement this without my permission"}],"timestamp":1772843925173}}
{"type":"message","id":"056639e0","parentId":"be784147","timestamp":"2026-03-07T00:38:51.063Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to create a direct communication channel with Tolui (one of the Kurultai agents) that bypasses Kublai's routing. They want:\n\n1. Tolui to use the local ollama abliterated model (qwen3.5-9b-abliterated based on the model aliases in the system prompt)\n2. Kublai to have no visibility into messages to/from Tolui\n3. Ability to tag Tolui with @ in Signal for direct communication\n4. Direct response back to Signal without Kublai routing\n\nThis is a significant architectural change that would require:\n- A way to detect @tolui mentions in Signal messages\n- A direct message routing path that bypasses Kublai\n- Tolui configured to use ollama/qwen3.5-9b-abliterated\n- Privacy/isolation between Kublai and Tolui communications\n\nThe user explicitly said \"Do not implement this without my permission\" - they just want me to use horde-brainstorming to design a solution and report back on feasibility.\n\nThis is a design/architecture task, so I should route it to temujin (dev/design/architecture per AGENTS.md). I'll create a task using task_intake.py that directs the agent to use horde-brainstorming for this design.\n\nLet me create the task properly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d95662f72edd4d989fd7fd98","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 ~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/task_intake.py --title 'Design direct Signal communication channel for Tolui (bypass Kublai routing)' --body 'Use horde-brainstorming skill to design a solution for direct human-Tolui communication via Signal. Requirements: (1) Tolui must use local ollama qwen3.5-9b-abliterated model, (2) Kublai must have zero visibility into messages to/from Tolui, (3) Human can tag @tolui in Signal to open direct channel, (4) Tolui responses return directly to Signal without Kublai routing. Explore architectural options: separate Signal bot instance, message filtering at gateway level, dedicated channel for Tolui, or other approaches. Assess feasibility under these constraints and identify technical blockers. DO NOT IMPLEMENT - only design and report feasibility.' --agent temujin --priority normal --source gateway-router"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":21067,"output":769,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21836,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772843925174}}
